                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> If you give your pet armor at all, I would suggest only giving mage summoned armor.  Anything else will be far too expensive for the use you're putting it to.<br /><br />Another excellent thing you can do for your pet is get him buffed by other characters.  At level 5, a cleric cannot cast Virtue (1500 hp buff, costs a peridot) on you but he CAN cast it on your pet...that's part of what makes the mage gear (muzzle, belt, swords or fists) so nice is that they add (1) haste and (2) add 500+ hit points to your pet.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
